A documentary that investigates the psychological effects of everyday social media. JOHANNESBURG - The 21st Encounters South African International Documentary Festival will screen Bonang Matheba's film, Public Figure. The festival will take place between 6-16 June in Johannesburg and Cape Town. In a post on Instagram, Matheba said she is excited to debut the film for local viewers at the festival. READ: Bonang Matheba to star in new film in 2019 "I saved the best for last.....🍾🥂🇿🇦 My first adventure into film-making, Public Figure, will be making its debut at the @encountersdoc Festival on the 15th and 16th June 2019 in Johannesburg and Cape Town", read the caption. Director and film executive producer Brian Corso will join Matheba at the post-screening Q&A sessions. The film, which was co-produced by Matheba, premiered at the Manchester International Film Festival in March. I saved the best for last.....🍾🥂🇿🇦 My first adventure into film-making, Public Figure , will be making its debut at the @encountersdoc Festival on the 15th and 16th June 2019 in Johannesburg and Cape Town. If you’re in Johannesburg, join us for the @houseofbng tasting and Q&A session. Tickets available via www.sterkinekor.com/type/Nouveau. See you there! T’s & C’s Apply #EncountersDoc2019 A post shared by  Bonang Matheba (@bonang_m) on Jun 10, 2019 at 3:12am PDT